==Translingual==

===Alternative forms===
* In Taiwan and Hong Kong, this character and its derived characters are written with {{l|mul|𦥑}} (7 strokes) as the upper component while in {{w|zh:新字形|mainland China}}, this character and its derivatives are written with {{l|mul|臼}} (6 strokes) as the upper component.
* A {{w|CJK Compatibility Ideographs|CJK compatibility ideograph}} exists at <code>U+2F837</code>''(composition: <small>{{l|mul|[[⿱申又]]}}</small>)'' and is encoded for a historical variant found in the Ming dynasty dictionary 《重訂直音篇》. <!-- Refer Page 35, Character no. 4 of https://archive.org/stream/02076767.cn#page/n34/mode/2up -->

